analysis: The documents primarily concern the modification, restoration, or transfer of land and property, often involving military reservations, naval facilities, or other government-controlled areas. Many documents involve adjustments to land descriptions, rights of way, or jurisdictions between different government entities or between the government and private entities. A recurring theme is the correction of errors in previous land descriptions and the adaptation of land use to changing needs.
title: Land Transfers and Boundary Adjustments for Military and Territorial Use
